Just removed the `functions` block — Vercel will auto-detect `api/chat.js` without it.

**Also check:** Go to your GitHub repo and make sure `api/chat.js` is at the **root level**, not inside another folder like `ironclad-jurist/api/chat.js`. Your repo structure should look like:
```
your-repo/
├── api/
│   └── chat.js      ← must be here at root
├── src/
│   ├── App.jsx
│   └── main.jsx
├── index.html
├── package.json
├── vercel.json
└── vite.config.js